body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, thank you for reaching out to Car Dealership Support. My name is Patrick Flores. May I have your name, please?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Nice to meet you, Jessica. To assist you better, may I please have your phone number?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, my number is five five five, two three four, nine zero one zero.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you. Can you also provide me with your address, please?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Of course, my address is three four seven, Elm Street, Apt one two three, Springfield.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for providing the information, Jessica. Is there anything else I can assist you with today?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: No, I think that's all. I appreciate your help.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: You're welcome, Jessica. Thank you for contacting Car Dealership Support. Should you need further assistance, feel free to reach out again. Have a great day!
